            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 8,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Appendix 1: Preliminary Equality Analysis"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 9,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.1,
                "text": "To provide a procedure for nuclear medicine staff referring patients for x-rays following nuclear medicine bone or lung studies."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 10,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.1,
                "text": "Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust is committed to the provision of a service that is fair, accessible and meets the needs of all individuals. (Refer to Appendix 1)"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 11,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 3.1,
                "text": "To reduce diagnostic delay in selected patients by referral to x-ray by nuclear medicine radiographic staff, within clearly defined parameters. This is by way of:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 12,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Further evaluation of any unexpected abnormal uptake of isotope in the organ examined and"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 13,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "In the absence of any recent plain x-ray imaging either at Broomfield or elsewhere which can be obtained by IEP (Image Exchange Portal) without undue delay, in order to issue a report in time for the management of patient, including pre-planned MDT discussions."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 14,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 3.2,
                "text": "To reduce delay in the assessment of the nuclear medicine scans either by a medical practitioner or appropriately qualified radiographer. This is by way of correlating the nuclear medicine scan findings with all other appropriate imaging modalities available and issue a report expeditiously to help with further management of the patient."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 15,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.1,
                "text": "All radiographers certified as nuclear medicine competent are qualified to follow this referral procedure."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 16,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "The x-rays will be limited to only include planar (non contrast) x-rays which can be performed in the x-ray department (not mobile examinations)."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.2,
                "text": "X-rays will only be requested when clinically indicated. The patient will be questioned as regards medical history of the area to be x-rayed, and the relevant information recorded on the request form."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.3,
                "text": "X-rays will only be requested after a full review of the patient's previous and planned imaging. X-rays will be requested from other hospitals via IEP if necessary and"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "appropriate. Every effort will be made to obtain these before re-imaging the patient."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.4,
                "text": "Referrals will be made within the Royal College of Radiologists guidelines."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.5,
                "text": "Referrals and safety forms will be scanned into the Radiology Information System (CRIS at time of writing)."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.1,
                "text": "All requests should be made on the Patient Administration System (Lorenzo at time of writing)"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.2,
                "text": "Standard views of the area will be taken. Additional projections may be taken at the discretion of the radiographer."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.3,
                "text": "Any difficulty with this process should be reported to the Clinical Lead Radiographer."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.1,
                "text": "Requests for x-ray must be referred electronically and include all patients' demographic information plus adequate clinical details to justify the request."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.2,
                "text": "Female patients must have the LMP (Last Menstrual Period) section completed where appropriate."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 27,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 28,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 8.1,
                "text": "All staff should follow Trust guidelines on infection prevention and control by ensuring that they effectively \u2018decontaminate their hands' before and after each patient contact."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 9.1,
                "text": "All requests are clinically justified by each Radiographer before any x-ray is undertaken. This means monitoring the system is continuous. The practitioner will contact the referring radiographer and the reason given for non compliance discussed. Any issues of non-compliance should be reported to the Lead NM Radiographer so that any training needs can be quickly resolved."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 10.1,
                "text": "Possible harm would be deemed to have occurred if the patient had already had a"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 31,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "medical exposure of that area in the recent past which would have been considered to be adequate for correlation and retrievable on PACS or via IEP from another Hospital."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "This would be considered an unintended exposure of ionising radiation, the RPS would"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 33,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "need to be informed and a DATIX incident generated."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 34,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 10.2,
                "text": "Any breach of the general radiology policies relating to IRMER regulations would need to be reported in the proscribed manner."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 35,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 11.1,
                "text": "A risk event form will be completed for any adverse outcomes, including unintended exposure of ionising radiation."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 36,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 11.2,
                "text": "All incidents and any trend analysis will be reviewed at the radiology audit meeting."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 37,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 11.3,
                "text": "All incidents reported to DATIX will be reviewed daily and investigated. Yearly DATIX analysis will be carried out to highlight any problem areas. These areas will then be assessed and appropriate adaptations made to prevent further breaches of policy."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 38,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 11.4,
                "text": "If further medical research produces changes to the national guidelines this policy will be updated to comply with the findings/recommendations."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 39,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2017.0,
                "text": "Ionising Radiation (Medical Exposure) Regulations"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 40,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Ionising Radiation (Medical Exposure) (Amendment) Regulations 2018 http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2018/contents/made"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 41,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Patient Dose Reduction in Diagnostic Radiology: Report by the 1990 Royal College of Radiologists and National Radiological Protection Board (Documents of the NRPB) National Radiological Protection Board 1990."
